&lt;p&gt;Cryopreservation is&nbsp;one of&nbsp;the methods of&nbsp;assisted reproduction. Its main purpose is&nbsp;to&nbsp;preserve high-quality, viable embryos, male and female gametes by&nbsp;means of&nbsp;cooling them to&nbsp;very low temperatures. Fast freezing or&nbsp;vitrification&nbsp;&mdash; one of&nbsp;cryopreservation techniques&nbsp;&mdash; helps to&nbsp;prevent ice crystals formation and increase survival rate of&nbsp;the frozen biomaterial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;When is&nbsp;cryopreservation used?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Freezing may be&nbsp;initiated by&nbsp;a&nbsp;patient or&nbsp;recommended by&nbsp;a&nbsp;fertility specialist. The procedure allows:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;preserving genetic material for a&nbsp;postponed pregnancy to&nbsp;reduce the risk of&nbsp;genetic defects in&nbsp;a&nbsp;future baby;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;increasing success rate in&nbsp;IVF programs;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;preserving fertility after chemotherapy of&nbsp;cancer tumors, removal of&nbsp;ovaries, or&nbsp;in&nbsp;the cases of&nbsp;early menopause;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;using biomaterial in&nbsp;gamete donation and surrogacy treatment programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What is&nbsp;the effect of&nbsp;cryopreservation on&nbsp;embryos and gametes?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The most sensitive to&nbsp;freezing are oocytes (eggs). They badly tolerate changes in&nbsp;the environment. Functional abilities of&nbsp;all kinds of&nbsp;biomaterial do&nbsp;not change or&nbsp;even improve a&nbsp;little after thawing. The period of&nbsp;storage may be&nbsp;unlimited but, in&nbsp;average, it&nbsp;is&nbsp;from 5&nbsp;to&nbsp;15&nbsp;years. The cost of&nbsp;freezing depends on&nbsp;the type of&nbsp;biological material and the cryopreservation method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The International Centre for Reproductive Medicine (ICRM) offers cryopreservation services in&nbsp;Saint-Petersburg including:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;sperm freezing;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;eggs and embryos vitrification;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;storage of&nbsp;biomaterial;&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;thawing after eggs and embryos vitrification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The specialists of&nbsp;our Centre work to&nbsp;help every couple that addressed&nbsp;us achieve happy parenthood.&lt;/p&gt;";}s:11:"'.chr(0).'*'.chr(0).'original";a:20:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"184";s:4:"NAME";s:16:"Cryopreservation";s:4:"CODE";s:16:"cryopreservation";s:7:"PICTURE";s:4:"2832";s:11:"DESCRIPTION";s:158:"Cryopreservation programs: sperm, eggs and embryos freezing and storage in our own cryobank - a safe way to keep your cells viable for future frozen transfers";s:16:"SECTION_PAGE_URL";s:27:"/services/cryopreservation/";s:9:"IBLOCK_ID";s:2:"90";s:16:"DESCRIPTION_TYPE";s:4:"html";s:11:"EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:14:"IBLOCK_TYPE_ID";s:11:"services_en";s:11:"IBLOCK_CODE";s:8:"services";s:18:"IBLOCK_EXTERNAL_ID";s:0:"";s:13:"GLOBAL_ACTIVE";s:1:"Y";s:4:"SORT";s:2:"40";s:7:"UF_ICON";s:6:"menu-6";s:15:"UF_SHOW_ON_MAIN";s:1:"0";s:17:"UF_SHOW_ON_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:8:"UF_VIDEO";N;s:20:"UF_SHOW_TYPES_PRICES";s:1:"0";s:14:"UF_DESCRIPTION";s:2364:"&lt;h2&gt;What is&nbsp;cryopreservation?&lt;/h2&gt;
